programme.desc: Spring time is an amazing time to be in the outdoors. Turkey hunting, crappie fishing, and good times with friends are hard to beat. Ty and Andy have a tradition of spending a weekend in Kansas each year and have found an incredible turkey hot spot.

programme.title: NEBRASKA

programme.title: SPRING RESOLVE

programme.title: CLOSE OUT
programme.desc: Ty's good friend Andy Gilliland is a Kansas resident and has done his due diligence on acquiring permission on properties in his area. Each year the guys get together to to hang out, hunt and get away from the fast pace of every day life.

programme.title: Turkey Creek
programme.desc: Looking to take advantage of the early archery season in Nebraska, Mike and Joey head west to hunt with our good friends at Heartland Pride Outfitters. While this area of Nebraska is known for the plethora of rios and hybrids, neither of them expected a hunt like this!

programme.title: Repeat Success
programme.desc: Skyler and Clayton typically kick off their turkey season in Kansas each year hunting the early archery season. Having hunted the same properties for the past several years, they typically have a great idea of where to start and after going back to back last year, they are excited to try and pull it off again.

programme.title: Back to Back
programme.desc: After a couple years of lower than usual turkey numbers, things seem to be on the rebound as Trent and Derek take to the field for the opening week of Kansas turkey season. Timing could not be any more perfect as the birds are fired up and in the perfect mood!

programme.title: 2 in 2
programme.desc: To start his season, Shawn heads to western Kansas to hunt with Midwest Land Group's Cole Shew. Having had success hunting deer in the past with Cole, Shawn was optimistic of what the week would hold and it did not disappoint!

programme.title: Just in Time
programme.desc: After a couple days of hunting and several close calls, Mike & the guys make a move to try to get in front of a group of birds mid-morning. As they scramble to set up, the birds round the bend and the guys are forced to hit the dirt to avoid being caught moving.

programme.title: Tempermental
programme.desc: The opening week of Missouri season has dealt Mike some very stubborn birds. Sometimes you can do everything just right and it doesn't seem to matter. 4 days into the season, after several heart-breaks, he finally finds a bird that wants to play rough and another that doesn't want to leave!

programme.title: Turf and Surf
programme.desc: It can be so frustrating when you are sure it's going to finally come together and the birds decide to do something completely different. On the flip side, all of that can change in the blink of an eye. After several close calls, Ty & Andy catch exactly the break they were looking for allowing them to tag out and head to the lake to fish!

programme.title: On A String
programme.desc: Each and every spring Ty makes it a point to spend some time hunting with his father and his daughter, but it's a rarity that he's able to hunt with them both at the same time. This year though, they were able to get out twice and the second time out was a hunt they won't soon forget!

programme.title: Payback
programme.desc: It seems like the last few springs have been a test with a declining turkey population and decoy shy birds. After many failed attempts, we finally came across the rights birds to commit to the decoys. We are hopeful that this is the turnaround that we have been looking for.

programme.title: Mixed Bag
programme.desc: Kicking off every turkey season in Kansas is something that Ty and Andy always look forward to. This year, however, was a little different in years past. They hunted hard, but failed to get birds to commit to the decoys during the early season. After finding some success in Missouri, they head back to KS for a shot at redemption.

programme.title: 90+ Turkeys In Our Decoys?!? (My First Nebraska Gobbler!)

This year they are looking for redemption for a rough season the year prior and man did it come together perfectly! Tag along on this intense Archery Turkey Hunt!

programme.title: Texas Gobbler Comes Screaming In & Beats Up My Decoy! (First Texas Rio)
programme.desc: Mike, Nate, Joey, Joel, and Brandon all head to Texas to meet up with their friend Caleb to try and harvest their first ever Texas Turkey's! After some unexpected weather it throws the Turkey's into a little funk that might make this trip harder than expected. Follow along as the guys test their luck on some Texas Rio's and maybe even a little Large Mouth Bass competition along the way!

programme.title: Chasing Turkeys & Giant Sheds in Colorado! (My Biggest Shed Ever!!)
programme.desc: Mike & Brandon head back to Colorado to meet up with their good friends Tony and Pete & Will. They have Deer and Turkey hunted with them over the past couple years and it has become a tradition to continue to come back. The turkeys are always fun to chase, but equally as exciting is the post season scouting for deer and picking up some Giant Colorado Whitetail Sheds!

programme.title: The Perfect Turkey Season: Filling 3 Tags with a Bow
programme.desc: Shawn and Rex have one of their best Archery Turkey seasons in Missouri filling 3 out of their 4 tags! Starting off opening day with an incredible hunt where Rex's bird smashes the decoy before Rex makes a perfect shot with a wild recovery. Then they set out to keep the hot streak going the rest of the season with two more incredible hunts and perfect archery shots on big mature Missouri Gobblers.

programme.title: Turkey Tag Out With A Bow! Some Of The Best Turkey Hunts I've Ever Had!
programme.desc: Mike has another unforgettable Turkey season in Missouri tagging out on two incredible Archery turkey hunts! Starting off with a close call he then follows up quickly with one wild hunt where he makes a perfect shot on a big mature gobbler that is on top of his decoy! After that it's a late morning gobbler that comes screaming in and Mike connects with him to fill his final tag!

programme.title: Completed the Spring Slam!! (Turkey, Morel Mushrooms, Deer Shed, & Crappie!)
programme.desc: To finish off the Missouri 3 Peat Rex connects with a gobbler when all had seemed to go wrong. To top it off he completes the Spring Slam by finding Morel Mushrooms, Finding a Deer Shed, and catching some Crappie! Great way to finish off the Missouri Turkey Season!

programme.title: Kansas Kickoff pt. 3
programme.desc: It's a gorgeous Kansas morning in early April and the Heartland Bowhunter crew are having no trouble finding gobblers.

programme.title: FULL STRUT SEASON 7 TRAILER
programme.desc: Season 7 of Full Strut

programme.title: All About The Kids
programme.desc: Legends of the Outdoors Hall of Famer, Phillip Vanderpool, introduces two new kids to the Outdoors at Triple H Outfitters in Kansas.

programme.title: Hunting Pheasants with Double Up Outfitters
programme.desc: Garry Mason, Jeff Milam, and Phillip Vanderpool join hall of famer Jerry Antley in North East Missouri on a Pheasant hunt with Double Up Outfitters.

programme.title: Slow down for more birds
programme.desc:
You set the pace in the field, and if you're in a rush so is your dog. That means less time in a scent cone and more missed birds.
Scott Linden of Wingshooting USA TV shows you how, and explains why, you should dial things down a bit when it comes to covering a field or covert.
If you want more tips on dog training and bird hunting, go to: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Hunting dog tailgate exam, part one
programme.desc:
Your best hunting partner needs some TLC ... especially after a hunt. wingshooting USA TV host Scott Linden provides the first part of three, helping you check him from nose tip to tail and ensure he's healthy, safe, and ready to go the next day.
Today, it's all about your dog's coat. We'll cover why it's important to get him off the ground, how "training" for the exam is critical, and what to look for from injuries to parasites. Your dog will stay healthier, well-rested, and ready to go the next day.
You'll also see some fun and exciting bird hunting footage from a hunt where the tailgate exam became crucial.

programme.title: Take a newcomer hunting - here's how
programme.desc:
Safety first, but then what? Author and TV host Scott Linden outlines some ways to encourage, motivate, and then help a new hunter on their first hunt.
From weather to shooting tips, to interacting with the dog, and what really counts on the hunt, Scott offers suggestions to ensure everyone has fun.
For more tips on hunting, dog training, and finding places to go: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Identify your best prospect for a new hunter
programme.desc:
Picking the right new hunting partner is an art and a science ... and while there's no wrong way, some ways are righter than others. Author/TV host Scott Linden outlines some tips on finding the right person, how to set expectations, and what to tell them - and show them - before you make "the ask."
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: The new-hunter best recruiter is your dog!
programme.desc:
Who doesn't love hunting dogs? The magic of their performance, excitement, and the adrenaline rush of a flush! One easy way to start a new hunter is to invite them to help train your dog.
Simple, short, convenient - there's no downside. And who wouldn't appreciate a little help with dog training?
Plus, some cool footage of a hunt with excellent dog works.
For more on starting a hunter, finding places to hunt, and dog training, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com.

programme.title: Ideas for finding new places to hunt
programme.desc:
Find upland birds on waterfowl production areas, and more tips on accessing public hunting areas are two of the topics ... as well as a great place to headquarter: Huron, South Dakota.
Watch some exciting bird hunting footage, too.
Find more information at www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Tailgate exam, part 2: wheels
programme.desc:
Part two covers your dog's "wheels," his feet. Enure a fantastic hunt tomorrow by keeping his feet healthy and injury-free with these step-by-step, toe-by-toe instructions.
Geet the entire exam in written form at HappyJackInc.com.

programme.title: Be nice, see where it gets you
programme.desc:
Walk-in hunting spots are not always easy to find. Here's an example of how to find them and the bonuses you might find along the way.
From hunting with a pro baseball player, to finding a black pheasant, to discovering new public-access spots in Huron, SD, there's a few lessons here.
Plus, some fun footage of a South Dakota pheasant hunt.
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Peak performance on Day Two: feed your dog strategically
programme.desc:
In the first 20 days of this season, my wirehair Flick had already hunted over 200 miles. He still scratches the RV door every morning, eager for another day of chukar chasing and quail quests.
I manage to keep up (mostly) with coffee and pain reliever. Flick, on the other paw, gets his stamina from Dr. Tim's dog food.
If your dog hunts multiple days in a row, it might be worth a look at how important food is to his performance. I asked Doctor Tim Hunt to share his thoughts on that, but first, a hunting story.

programme.title: Tailgate exam, Part 3: His steering wheel
programme.desc:
Okay, we've checked his body, his feet. But the tailgate exam isn't over until you've checked a dog's head – the steering wheel of your hunting machine. Like your truck, you're not getting very far without one! Put off that tall cold one for a couple more minutes. You'll have a fully-functioning hunting partner for the next day … and you won't die of thirst!
In this video, I'll show you where to look, what to look for and why ... and also how to remedy most common issues that might kibosh your next day's hunt, from getting stuff out of eyes and ears, to ensuring weeds and crud stay outta those places and more!
I'll take you step-by-step through all the deep, dark places that harbor danger and irritation on your dog's head so he's ready and rested for the next day's hunt.
And if you need remedies for any of the problems outlined, you can find them at www.happyjackinc.com.

programme.title: Get high, become a better bird hunter
programme.desc:
Not like that! I mean, boost your altitude - even just a bit - and you'll be able to keep a closer eye on your dog. If you're paying attention, you'll have a crucial half-second extra to get ready for a safe, sure shot.
I'll show you how - what you might use to get "up there" a little, what to look for in your dog's behavior, and why it's worth the effort.

programme.title: What's in my vest ... and why
programme.desc:
"Don't leave home without" is more than a cliche' from a TV commercial. What should you take on your next bird hunt, for you and your dog? Here's some advice on critical stuff, and what you might leave home ... without jeopardizing your safety or comfort - or you're dog's!
Somewhere in my personal vest is everything I need to shoot as well as possible (no smart remarks, please), stay found or get found, keep my dog safe and healthy, and help me survive a night or two in an emergency.
I'll show you all of it, and how to keep it from getting lost somewhere in the middle of nowhere!

programme.title: Your dog hurts - here's why
programme.desc:
I seem to be getting a lot of related questions since the season ended – most about aches and pains in our four-footed hunting buddies. And us!
The difference is, dogs won't show it like we do, with gripes and limping, complaints and wincing. They are way too loyal and hard working. It's why we love 'em.
You might already know this, but veterinarians tell me dogs seldom show pain. What they do, is slow down. Their pace in the field drags, they're slow to get out of their crate.
Maybe they won't jump onto your tailgate or training table.
That's probably arthritis, and it affects most dogs over eight years old. But here's the scary part: twenty percent of dogs show signs as early as one year old.
In this video, I'll show you how to prevent arthritis, manage it if your dog already has it, and what to avoid so he doesn't get it prematurely!

programme.title: Fuel your bird dog's peak performance ... but NOT with carbs!
programme.desc:
We hunt to watch our dogs work. So, stand by for plenty of that. But first, let me relate my last season. I tracked Flick's mileage. He averaged twenty-five miles a day, over almost fifty days in the field. I'm a lousy shooter, and okay trainer … so I'll attribute his stamina to my dumb luck, and his performance dog food.
If you want to watch your dog in the field day after day, heed some of the advice I got from Doctor Tim Hunt, a veterinarian, sled dog racer, and developer of the food Flick eats. He says the fuel you put in your dog directly impacts his ability to hunt hard, especially on a long hunting trip. He should know. His food has powered a bunch of Iditarod winners … and my guy Flick.
In this video, you'll learn what the key ingredients are in a dog food, how they work, and why. Hint: the most important component in your dog food is probably NOT what you think it is.

programme.title: Bird dog training: one (baby) step at a time
programme.desc: Dogs learn in a linear fashion, so in this video Scott shows you how important it is to break a complex task into smaller pieces. Training one piece at a time ensures a compliant, happy, peak-performing hunting buddy.

programme.title: My First Outfitter
programme.desc: Stephen and Cliff get the opportunity to head to Kentucky for the early season opener and a chance at harvesting a buck in velvet.

programme.title: Sweet Redemption
programme.desc: Season 6 Episode 3 - Cliff heads to Whiskey River Whitetail looking to put a tag on a Kentucky velvet buck.

programme.title: Kentucky Opener, The Journey Begins
programme.desc: Jared Mills and Grant Noble head to Kentucky for their first hunts of the year. Brandon Whitten begins the quest for Buster, and Bella Reed takes a big framed 8 point during the Iowa youth season.

programme.title: Bowhunting In City Limits, First Cold Front Of The Year
programme.desc: On this week's episode we catch up with Tyler Behlmann and Justin Luebrecht, the first cold front of the year brings some solid action to the guys. Then, Max Mongrello gives an update on his urban hunts!

programme.title: Early And Late
programme.desc: Pro Staffer Adam Nicolas hunts a 6-year-old bruiser deer named Mutt. Shiloh Butts takes a deer just before the season ends.

programme.title: Strength In Weakness
programme.desc: Michael Harrell hunts a monster 180-inch deer in Oklahoma with his bow in early season.

programme.title: Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: We give you a behind the scenes look at FDO and cameramen Trent Gaines and Johnny Maxwell hunt big Oklahoma and Texas whitetail.

programme.title: Seared Sturgeon
programme.desc: Fresh from the Lake Winnebago system in east-central Wisconsin, Lake Sturgeon are a rare delicacy. More common than not they are smoked, but what if we told you there's this other way to prepare sturgeon that will leave your guests in disbelief? Try this awesome recipe and you won't be disappointed!

programme.title: Venison Backstrap w/Fire Melted Bleu Cheese and Bacon
programme.desc: Alakan Sitka Deer backstraps grilled over mesquite lump coal and drizzled over by fire melted blue cheese and crumbled smoked bacon. Try this with any venison backstrap and savor every bite!

programme.title: Cedar Plank Great Lakes King Salmon
programme.desc: Salmon is hard to cook wrong, but it's also hard to cook just right. This is our favorite recipe of all the different ways to cook salmon and it is super easy. Cedar, smoke, Rosemary and Thyme. Bring on the compliments after you serve this to your guests!

programme.title: Venison Hangover Burger w/Quail Eggs
programme.desc: This is one of our absolute best burger recipe we've ever served up. We use whitetail venison for this video and pair it up with grilled sweet onion, Nueske's smoked bacon, smokehouse cheddar and provolone, along with a trio of sunny-side up quail eggs on top. Oh, and let's not forget a little bit of barbecue sauce to dress it up a little more. Perfection in a toasted bun!

programme.title: Seared Sturgeon
programme.desc: Fresh from the Lake Winnebago system in east-central Wisconsin, Lake Sturgeon are a rare delicacy. More common than not they are smoked, but what if we told you there's this other way to prepare sturgeon that will leave your guests in disbelief? Try this awesome recipe and you won't be disappointed!

programme.title: Cranberry Elk Stuffed Acorn Squash
programme.desc: Watch Chef Shelly utilize wild elk in a recipe for Cranberry Elk Stuffed Acorn Squash. She uses an interesting spice combination to create Moroccan spices for this fall dish. Perfect for this time of year. Plus she shares tips on how to prepare this a day in advance then bring together as a fun dinner party idea.

programme.title: Espresso Antelope Tenderloin
programme.desc: Antelope tenderloin is one of the leanest and easiest proteins to cook. In this episode Chef Shelly pan sears her antelope tenderloins with an espresso spice rub. Another interesting tip she shares is about which vegetable pairs perfectly with coffee rubs and why.

programme.title: Grouse Alfredo
programme.desc: Chef Shelly shows an easy recipe for Alfredo using wild harvested Spruce Grouse. Especially comforting meal for when you're home alone while your spouse is out hunting. In addition she makes a homemade mayo for her Caesar Dressing that's so healthy & easy it'll replace store bought.

programme.title: Balsamic Marinated Elk
programme.desc: Watch Chef Shelly bring the forest to your table. In this episode she shows you a different way to cook all those lean wild game roasts. Chef Shelly pan sears wild Elk eye of round with a Balsamic Marinade. Then shows you how to reduce that marinade into a sauce and serve with one of her signature side dishes.

programme.title: Blackened Salmon
programme.desc: Wild salmon is the star of this episode. Chef Shelly explains how & why she pairs specific side dishes with her Cajun spiced Blackened Salmon recipe. These sides make the dish well rounded with easy composed flavors that compliment each other. Tune in and learn her cooking tips & tricks.

programme.title: Caramelized Bacon Onion Jam Bison Burgers
programme.desc: Don't miss this mouth-watering episode where Chef Shelly prepares a jazzed up Montana Bison Burger with Caramelized Bacon Onion Jam. She also shares her tricks & tips for easy individual one-crust apple pie for dessert. These are sure to become new recipe favorites in your kitchen as well.

programme.title: Parmesan Crusted Pheasant
programme.desc: Chef Shelly shares family stories while showing how to increase moisture & tenderness in dryer game cuts like this UNIQUE recipe for Pheasant Parmesan. She shows her easy quick brine technique. Then the side dish she pairs with it is her Bloody Mary Polenta. You'll want this recipe in your weekly meal rotation, trust me!

programme.title: Duck Fat Biscuits & Elk Irish Stew
programme.desc: Wild Elk is used for this easy yet comforting recipe. You don't want to miss the Duck Fat Biscuits that make the best side dish to Chef Shelly's Elk Irish Stew. Lots of tips & tricks in this episode on how to make flaky biscuits. Plus using different cuts of elk for different uses. Stay tuned while Chef Shelly brings the forest to your table - with duck fat biscuits!

programme.title: Slow Braised Antelope Shank
programme.desc: So many wild game butchers throw the shank away, or trim and grind into burger. Chef Shelly shows you a better way to enjoy these bone-in cuts with one of her signature dishes. Red Wine Braised Antelope Shank paired with side dishes that compliment the richness of the recipe. She uses the bone marrow with this low & slow braise technique and adds it to the reduced liquid for a rich gravy.

programme.title: Huckleberry Emu & Wild Rice
programme.desc: Considered the Filet Mignon of game. Emu meat is tender and flavorful. Chef Shelly shows how to prepare it to medium-rare as its a red meat bird. The Montana Huckleberry also makes a star appearance in this recipe with a Savory Huckleberry Sauce. Chef Shelly pairs this with Wild Rice Pilaf and her secret to cooking this wild harvested seed.

programme.title: Shelly's Elk Enchilada Casserole
programme.desc: In this episode Chef Shelly shares the first recipe that started her wild game cooking endeavors over 30 years ago. It's a family staple and always great for hunting camp as well. Shelly gets requests for these every year from her husband's buddies to enjoy at Elk Camp.

programme.title: Shelly's Nilgai Shawarma
programme.desc: South Texas Antelope (aka Nilgai) is the star ingredient in this Season 2 episode. Chef Shelly uses a 21 day Aged Leg Filet Steak to show you how to make a spicier version of the Greek Gyro in this Shawarma recipe. Easier to do on the cooktop, no need for the traditional vertical rotisserie. Plus its a new Quick & Easy weeknight meal you'll want to repeat over and over.

programme.title: Elk Spaghetti Squash
programme.desc: A quick, simple and healthy recipe that replaces starchy pasta with Spaghetti Squash. Then Chef Shelly makes an easy meat sauce with wild elk burger and homemade tomato sauce. This recipe can be modified for many different diets. Its gluten-free as is but if you omit the meat & cheese you can make it vegetarian and add more mushrooms and veg.

programme.title: Cognac Mushrooms & Leeks with Grilled South Texas Antelope
programme.desc: Going back to her Restaurant days, Chef Shelly shows how to do Cognac Mushrooms & Leeks to go with her grilled South Texas Antelope Leg Filet Steak. She also shares some juicy grilling techniques that will change how you crosshatch. Find out why this episode had the crew asking for locations of fire extinguishers.

programme.title: Offaly Delicious Antelope Pate
programme.desc: Must see TV with this Offaly Delicious Antelope Pate that Chef Shelly gently cooks with Sous Vide method to ensure it highlights the best qualities of game meat. This is great for party appetizers, served with an Apple Onion Compote over toast points. You'll never look at offal the same again.

programme.title: Antelope Wellington
programme.desc: Watch how Chef Shelly makes a Wild upscale recipe with South Texas Antelope. This amazing Antelope Wellington utilizes some of her Antelope Pate from the previous episode. This is a WOW dish with several tips & tricks on how to properly cook your game meat for a Wellington.

programme.title: Ribeye of The Sky
programme.desc: Chef Shelly cooks up Sandhill Crane (aka: Ribeye of the Sky) in this episode. You'll love learning about this red meat bird that looks and tastes like beef. Shelly shares some great tips on making the "best mashed potatoes ever" to pair with this Ribeye of the Sky steak.

programme.title: Fly Fishing & Pike Veracruz with Cilantro Lime Rice
programme.desc: Chef Shelly shows how to make an invasive species in the Montana rivers, Northern Pike, delicious. Its not just for tacos anymore. While explaining this easy fish recipe she visits with Lauren Karnopp of @thefebruaryroom Podcast. Afterwards Shelly gets a fly fishing lesson from Justin Karnopp of CD Fishing USA on the Bitterroot River.

programme.title: Montana Gumbo with Wild Boar & Quail
programme.desc:
In this episode Chef Shelly creates a Montana Gumbo using Wild Boar Sausage and Quail Legs. It is applauded by the crew as Atchafalaya Ready. Which is apparently Louisiana code for "real deal" gumbo. Don't miss this episode with tips about roux. Also, how to tell the difference between Cajun and Creole cooking, plus so much more.
Chef Shelly is using Broken Arrow Ranch Wild and Pure game meat from Texas in this episode.

programme.title: Wild Mushroom Foraging for Pheasant Marsala with Morels
programme.desc: Chef Craig joins Shelly in this episode and shares his mushroom foraging skills and insights. Lots of great tips on which trees they grow under, temperatures to wait for, and so much more. Then Craig comes back to the kitchen with Chef Shelly while she prepares her Wild Pheasant Marsala using some foraged wild Morel mushrooms. This episode shows a trick to ensure dry lean cuts of game retain moisture.

programme.title: Pheasant & Wild Rice Soup
programme.desc:
Don't make me go Beth Dutton on you! Talking all things Montana and the TV show Yellowstone in this episode.
Chef Shelly is cooking with her friend and Bitterroot Valley Real Estate Broker, Kathie Butts, sharing insights into what it takes to do real estate in Montana.
Chef Shelly shows how to make a healthier version of an old recipe from her restaurant.

programme.title: Axis Meatballs with Spicy Orange Chile Sauce
programme.desc: Axis Deer is highly desired for its flavor. Chef Shelly's unique meatball recipe that she uses for game meat is one you won't want to miss. Plus in this episode she shares her most requested sauce recipe. Whether for a group of friends or for a comforting meal this Axis Meatball with Asian Orange Chile Sauce is one to hold onto and make again and again.

programme.title: Shelly's Orange Cardamom Roast Pheasant
programme.desc: Pheasant gets a bad rap for being dry when cooked. In this Season 3 opener of Shelly's Game Kitchen you'll learn about the brine technique to add moisture to dry game. With Chef Shelly's Orange Cardamom Roast Pheasant recipe you'll become a better upland bird cook and learn the tips and techniques to make it easier.

programme.title: Shelly's Whole Roast Wild Turkey
programme.desc: Whole Roast Wild Turkey is on the menu in this episode of Shelly's Game Kitchen. Her technique adds flavor and moisture to a traditionally dry protein. Learn the best way to counteract any flavor profiles you may want to overcome in your wild turkey with these tips. Additionally, as a newly diagnosed diabetic, Chef Shelly shares her version of a low carb dressing.

programme.title: Herb Dijon Venison Tenderloin
programme.desc: Chef Shelly whips up a Herb Dijon Tenderloin in this episode. An easy and scrumptious meal using a Montana 270 muley. Try this rub on other meat cuts too. Then she shows you how to make a perfect risotto with technique and tips.

programme.title: Shelly's Antelope Heart Steaks
programme.desc:
One of the healthiest proteins is heart, but how you prep and cook it really determines its flavor. Chef Shelly shows you her technique for Antelope Heart Steaks. She pairs it with a common mispronounced side dish that is a high-protein grain.
Chef Shelly, as a diabetic, shows how to utilize products with low-glycemic indexes, without sacrificing flavor.

programme.title: Shelly's Kung Pao Pheasant
programme.desc: This is a great recipe for a quick, fast, and a little spice, for a weeknight meal. Chef Shelly shows a common Chinese technique to make melt in your mouth proteins for Wok stir frying. This Kung Pao recipe has a few different twists than the traditional dish, of course Chef Shelly had to "Montana-fy" it. Enjoy her version, bringing the forest to your table, with Shelly's Kung Pao Pheasant.

programme.title: Mediterranean Rabbit
programme.desc:
A new and creative recipe for rabbit that will delight your tastebuds. Chef Shelly whips up a Mediterranean Braised Wild Rabbit in this episode of Shelly's Game Kitchen. With techniques on best ways to avoid gamey tastes, plus other helpful cooking tips.
You won't want to miss out on learning this easy recipe. With rich rabbit flavors enhanced by the brine of olives and capers served with lemon oregano orzo.

programme.title: Shelly's Zinfandel Elk Roast
programme.desc:
In this episode Chef Shelly shows an easy and fast technique for cooking those elk roasts. With a pressure cooker you achieve a tender roast in a short amount of time.
Tune in as she also describes how to make homemade Mac-n-Cheese and the secret ingredient that makes all cream based sauces sing.

programme.title: Shelly's Hunter Bars
programme.desc:
When prepping for your next hunt be sure to think about how many calories you're burning while hiking/hunting. In this episode, Chef Shelly is sharing her Hunter "Protein" Bars.
As a newly diagnosed diabetic, Chef Shelly understands better than most the dangers of not being prepared and over-exerting without replenishing calories. This delicious and healthy protein bar is a great homemade version that is less sugary, with a lower glycemic index than store bought. Keep in the freezer until you're ready to hunt or hike.

programme.title: Shelly's Grouse Saltimbocca
programme.desc: Tune in and discover your next favorite dish! Chef Shelly shows her simple recipe for Grouse Saltimbocca. It's a classic Italian dish with a little "Shelly" spin. She pairs this with Spaghetti Aglio e Olio, another classic Italian dish. The richness of Saltimbocca pairs perfectly with the light garlic olive oil sauce of the spaghetti.

programme.title: Season 4 Teaser
programme.desc:
Here's a preview of what's coming up in Season 4 of On-the-Road with Shelly's Game Kitchen.
Get ready for mouthwatering recipes featuring Oryx, Tundra Swan, Partridge, Bear, and many more.

programme.title: Strawberry Glazed Tundra Swan
programme.desc: In a very special episode, Jana Waller Bair of Skull Bound Chronicles asked Chef Shelly to create a recipe for her Tundra Swan. Watch for tips & techniques for her Wild Strawberry Glazed Tundra Swan.

programme.title: Campfire Creamed Pheasant
programme.desc:
Hang out with Chef Shelly Meyer as she whips up a cozy Creamed Pheasant dish over a crackling campfire. Even with some wildlife interruptions, Chef Shelly will walk you through making this family favorite one-pot meal.
Shelly shares the mishaps of their RV travels toward fulfilling a year-long dream to hike one of Utah's stunning landscapes. Enjoy the friendly vibes, fun stories, and delicious food that make this episode a must-watch.

programme.title: Double Smoked Elk Spring Rolls
programme.desc:
Oh YEAH! Chef Shelly and Mike Starr of Blazing Star BBQ, get smoking in this mouth-watering episode. Enjoy this refreshing and delicious Double Smoked Elk Spring Roll recipe with TWO sauces that Mike described as, "A fusion of Asian flavors."
Shelly shares her tried and true tips for making a practical hunting or hiking lunch using leftovers. Creativity abounds in this collaborative episode that is a must-watch.

programme.title: VENISON & CARBONTV DUO
programme.desc:
Julie McQueen, CEO of Carbon TV, joins Chef Shelly in the kitchen for a fun and creative cooking session. With a last minute guest increase, Shelly boosted meal preparations to create a Mixed Grill. This is a tale of two states, two venisons, two sauces & two sides that created such a harmonious meal, its still reminisced months later.
Join the joy and laughter only possible among treasured friends in this must watch episode.

programme.title: Hunter Ed Certified! / Our Wyld Life / EP3
programme.desc: In EP 3, Kristy and Yogi collect some water samples from the new property to have tested. The baby mules are back and they're as wild as ever...the training is such a rewarding process! Kristy and Yogi also spend three days getting their Wyoming Hunter Ed certification, as well as their Instructor Certification! Exciting times...this is, Our Wyld Life!

programme.title: Western Hunting & Conservation Expo / Our Wyld Life / EP1
programme.desc:
Welcome to Our Wyld Life where host Kristy Titus and her husband, Yogi, take viewers along on their day-to-day lives, full of adventure. After relocating to Wyoming, hunting, outdoor and shooting sports recreation are literally in their backyard. The couple is truly making their home on the range while developing their new homestead and enjoying life in the cowboy state.
In our premiere episode, we show you a little bit of what it's like being a Wyoming resident, in the winter. After a tough start, Kristy makes it a great week with familiar faces and many new ones, in what is one of the most fun shows of the year! If you didn't make it in 2023, it's a must to attend next year! Also, you'll be introduced to the newest (and longest eared) members of the family! Kristy shows off her baby mules...lots more of the mules to come! When they aren't out on an adventure trekking deep into the backcountry with their horses and mules, you'll find them preparing for the next opportunity to do so.
Our Wyld Life presents the journey of life out west in Wyoming.

programme.title: DOUBLE DOUBLE
programme.desc: Chris and Parker Gade and other family members head to Wyoming on a DIY antelope hunt!! They had a double double good time!!

programme.title: BIG POND BRUISERS
programme.desc: Lee Schneider and Zach Haas are heading back out onto Lake Michigan with Captain Fluffy in search of king salmon, coho, rainbows, or whatever else wants to bite!! Once we hit that magic hour, the action was non-stop!!!

programme.title: What are the Chances
programme.desc:
Luke Cranney has been guiding sheep in Idaho for 11 years, and packing in Alaska for 2. Everything lined up, and he got the chance to go on a hunt of his own. However, unlike many sheep hunts they had no scouting or plan in place. This was a true adventure hunt filled with bad weather, beautiful animals, and uncanny good luck. Follow Luke, Austin and Brady on an experience they will never forget.
Visit huntinfool.com for all your western hunting needs. Hunt Consulting | Magazine | Draw Odds | 3D mapping | Outfitter Referrals | License Application | Hunt Giveaways
Instagram: @huntinfool_official Facebook: @thehuntinfool Twitter: @huntinfool

programme.title: COLORADO BIGHORN EXPERIENCE - with Aaron Derose of Dillinger River Outfitters
programme.desc: After 23 years of applying for the Colorado Bighorn Aaron Derose has the opportunity of a lifetime. We hope you enjoy as Aaron pursues one of the truly most majestic animals in North America.

programme.title: The Nosler Experience, Alaskan Moose with Dillinger Outfitters
programme.desc: Garret Wales and John Nosler go after Giant Alaskan Moose with Dillinger Outfitters.

programme.title: Largest Public Land Ram in Utah 194"
programme.desc: We were very fortunate to play a roll in capturing Kyle Ekker's hunt on film. Kyle Ekker grew up in Green River Utah where he developed his love of hunting, chasing mulies on the Book Cliffs. He has worked for the Emery County Sheriff's Office for 30 years where he is currently employed as a captain. He has been a member of the Utah FNAWS for the last 10 years and through this he is able to share his passion for the outdoors & wild sheep. In December of 2015 he drew the highly coveted Rocky Mountain Bighorn Sportsman's permit. This tag gave him the opportunity to hunt sheep from the beginning of September to December 31st on almost any open units in the state. He hunted every opportunity that he had he could in pursuit of his dream ram. On November 30th things came together for him and he was able to harvest a very magnificent ram. With an unofficial green score of 194" this ram will be the largest public land ram ever killed in the state of Utah.

programme.title: Leopard Hunting at Mt. Galai Tanzania

programme.title: Cape Buffalo Charge
programme.desc: Black Death is an accurate description of the very deadly Cape Buffalo. One of Africa's "Big 5", this massive beast is mean, unforgiving, and a very dangerous animal to hunt! The thrill of the stalk of one of these monsters fuels J. Alain Smith's passion for big game hunting like no other! Every hunt is different, every hunt is risky, and every hunt is completely thrilling! Watch now and follow the adventure!

programme.title: Hunting with a Lost Lemming: Okayest Hunter's 2022 deer hunting season kickoff!
programme.desc:
The crew from the Okayest Hunter podcast thought it'd be a good idea to start a hunting show, but they wanted to do something different, and it needed to align with the brand, mission, and ethos of the Okayest Hunter. Basically, it can't be too serious. So we thought, hey, let's make the "Office" show, but for hunting.
Our hunting season is chock full of humility as we miss place things, take too long to pick out our tree, injure ourselves, miss deer, lose arrows, and more. However, we had one of our best and most fun seasons yet! Follow along as we release new episodes as our 2022 deer hunting season unfolds. We assure you it'll be worth getting all the way to the end!
Cheers to chasing shooter bucks in the deer woods and never passing on what makes you happy! We hope you can relate as we share our shenanigans with everyone!
Okayest Hunter Show, season one: We'll See How it Goes, Episode one: Hunting with a lost lemming.

Non-stop bowfishing action as the Giants of Green Bay move into the shallows and make for some great night time bowfishing.

Fight to Survive - S03:E04 - Treestand Nightmare
programme.desc: When avid bow hunter, Dr. Joe Baumgardner sets out to do routine maintenance on his tree stands, a twenty two foot fall leaves him with a severely broken leg and miles from help in the deep Mississippi woods.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E05 - Crushed by a Boulder Part 1
programme.desc: While solo climbing Mt. Goddard, a remote peak in the California Sierra, Gregg Hein's leg is crushed by a boulder and he's sent careening down the mountain. Barely able to stop his fall, he's now faced with a horrific compound fracture.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E06 - Crushed by a Boulder Part 2
programme.desc: After his leg is crushed by a boulder, Gregg Hein is stranded on a high Sierra peak with an infected compound fracture. Knowing he won't be reported missing for days, Gregg attempts to crawl off the mountain and rescue himself.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E06 - All Eyes On Us
programme.desc: Chris and Casey Keefer are back at it, catching fish for dinner and getting closer to being able to leave. But things get tense when a grizzly bear wanders too close to their campsite, putting both brothers in danger!

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E07 - Salmon Island
programme.desc: Now that most of the waterfowl have headed further south for migration, brothers Chris and Casey Keefer are putting their efforts into fishing to get the calories they need. They're heading back downriver after packing up camp, zeroing in on an area they think has several moose.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E08 - Log Jammed
programme.desc: While the brothers get closer to a part of the river packed with moose, they face a bunch of problems. They have to find a way around and carry their stuff over a huge pile of logs that could mess up their hunt, possibly pushing them into a part of the river they weren't ready for.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E09 - Bull In The Bush
programme.desc: After more than three weeks trekking through moose country, brothers Chris and Casey Keefer finally set up camp in a new spot and almost immediately come face-to-face with a massive bull.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E10 - End Of The Line
programme.desc: With the odds piling against them, the 80-mile river adventure is almost over, and brothers Chris and Casey Keefer have one final opportunity to find an Alaskan moose just a few miles from where they'll be picked up at the river junction.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E06 - On the Move
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven leave camp Hell Hole and hit the trail again. They are headed for lower elevation in search of a more permanent place to call home.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E07 - Permanent Residence
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven find a long term camping spot out fo the snow and at a lower elevation. Laramy gets to work making a more permanent shelter and looking for food.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E08 - Focused on Food
programme.desc: Laramy locates some whitetail deer and focuses his efforts on hunting them.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E09 - Thriving
programme.desc: Stocked up on food, Laramy and Seven thrive in their new location. Laramy focuses on building some amenities to make life easier on The Trail.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E10 - Return Home
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven say goodbye to their final camp and head back home.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E02 - Nightmare Canyon Part 2

As night falls and temperatures drop to freezing time is critical if the brothers are to survive.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E03 - Under the Desert Sun
programme.desc: Ed Rosenthal set out for a short hike in Joshua Tree National Park, but in the heat of the day he became turned around and lost. His six-day ordeal of survival in blazing temperatures with no food or water is nothing short of miraculous.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E04 - Treestand Nightmare
programme.desc: When avid bow hunter, Dr. Joe Baumgardner sets out to do routine maintenance on his tree stands, a twenty two foot fall leaves him with a severely broken leg and miles from help in the deep Mississippi woods.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E05 - Crushed by a Boulder Part 1
programme.desc: While solo climbing Mt. Goddard, a remote peak in the California Sierra, Gregg Hein's leg is crushed by a boulder and he's sent careening down the mountain. Barely able to stop his fall, he's now faced with a horrific compound fracture.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E06 - Crushed by a Boulder Part 2
programme.desc: After his leg is crushed by a boulder, Gregg Hein is stranded on a high Sierra peak with an infected compound fracture. Knowing he won't be reported missing for days, Gregg attempts to crawl off the mountain and rescue himself.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E06 - All Eyes On Us
programme.desc: Chris and Casey Keefer are back at it, catching fish for dinner and getting closer to being able to leave. But things get tense when a grizzly bear wanders too close to their campsite, putting both brothers in danger!

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E07 - Salmon Island
programme.desc: Now that most of the waterfowl have headed further south for migration, brothers Chris and Casey Keefer are putting their efforts into fishing to get the calories they need. They're heading back downriver after packing up camp, zeroing in on an area they think has several moose.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E08 - Log Jammed
programme.desc: While the brothers get closer to a part of the river packed with moose, they face a bunch of problems. They have to find a way around and carry their stuff over a huge pile of logs that could mess up their hunt, possibly pushing them into a part of the river they weren't ready for.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E09 - Bull In The Bush
programme.desc: After more than three weeks trekking through moose country, brothers Chris and Casey Keefer finally set up camp in a new spot and almost immediately come face-to-face with a massive bull.

programme.title: Dropped - S03:E10 - End Of The Line
programme.desc: With the odds piling against them, the 80-mile river adventure is almost over, and brothers Chris and Casey Keefer have one final opportunity to find an Alaskan moose just a few miles from where they'll be picked up at the river junction.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E06 - On the Move
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven leave camp Hell Hole and hit the trail again. They are headed for lower elevation in search of a more permanent place to call home.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E07 - Permanent Residence
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven find a long term camping spot out fo the snow and at a lower elevation. Laramy gets to work making a more permanent shelter and looking for food.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E08 - Focused on Food
programme.desc: Laramy locates some whitetail deer and focuses his efforts on hunting them.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E09 - Thriving
programme.desc: Stocked up on food, Laramy and Seven thrive in their new location. Laramy focuses on building some amenities to make life easier on The Trail.

programme.title: The Trail - S01:E10 - Return Home
programme.desc: Laramy and Seven say goodbye to their final camp and head back home.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E12 - The New Royals
programme.desc: Princesses Beatrice and Eugenie have gone through a lot of media attention and tough situations in their lives. From their parents' very public split to being targeted by the press, they've been through quite a bit. Despite all this, they remain dedicated to supporting the monarchy with their charity work. Through serving the Commonwealth, both sisters continue to make a positive impact.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E07 - Operation Spotted Dog
programme.desc: Working to protect our treasured natural resources in some of the country's most secluded spots means there's never a boring day on the job.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E08 - Operation Boat Float
programme.desc: In the shade of the wild mountains, the Yellowstone River transforms into a colorful spectacle during the yearly boat float weekend. Armed with jet boats, the Wardens gear up for a wild time, looking out for the river and helping out the wacky rafters.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E10 - Return Home
programme.desc: Casey’s bull disappeared downstream quickly, heading into uncharted waters the brothers hadn’t explored yet. They’re eager to see what happens next.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E05 - Juno, Cassini and Beyond
programme.desc: The Cassini space craft has completed its mission over Saturn, Juno has reached its target and has commenced its scientific observations of the giant planet Jupiter. and The New Horizons speeds on it its next encounter at the edge of the solar system.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E06 - Sling Shot
programme.desc: Sending probes throughout the solar system is a mathematicians dream and an engineers nightmare, sling shotting probes around other planets to arrive at their destination, we checkout the latest probes about to slingshot about the solar system.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E09 - Private Military Contractors
programme.desc: The practice of hiring private armies goes back to ancient times, and the mystique associated with the mercenary warrior has been the subject of many historical studies and fictional characterizations. This episode of CQB takes a more contemporary look at a day in the life of a group of civilian contractors, and how their role has evolved on the modern battlefield. Using its “sub-second” analysis techniques and intimate first-person footage, CQB reveals the backgrounds, training and equipment of today’s “soldiers for hire” and how private armies are re-shaping the way conflicts are conducted around the world.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E10 - Close Protection
programme.desc: From the elite ex-special forces personnel in charge of guarding heads of state in conflict zones to the two-person teams that protect CEOs in dangerous regions, modern day bodyguards must be well versed in close quarter battle techniques. An immense amount of planning and preparation is involved in each operation. From air travel, car convoys and helicopter shuttles to basic foot traffic, a close protection squad must be completely tuned to the Who, What, Where and When of any given situation. This episode of CQB focuses on the complex day-to-day and minute-to-minute operations of these elite teams and the highly developed techniques they employ.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E04 - The Bears that Couldn't Be
programme.desc: Temperate Rain Forest. Jim and Corey search for an epic hunting spot deep in the coastal rain forest of Vancouver Island that Jim last explored 20 years ago.

programme.desc: Meghan Markle and Prince Harry share similar interests and seem like a perfect match. Both have faced tough times growing up but have come out on top. Now they're winning together. This hour-long special, featuring a chat with author Andrew Morton, explores the social backdrop that makes their bold marriage fit right in with today's British Royal Family.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E08 - Cosmic Collisions
programme.desc: Cosmic and x rays, these mysterious and highly powerful particles from deep space are being investigated to finally discover where they come from.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E11 - Counter Terrorism
programme.desc: Following the September 11 attacks, military presence became commonplace in New York and other American cities, and the counter terrorism forces were effectively given a “blank cheque” when it came to ensuring that another terrorist incident would never take place on American soil. This episode of CQB takes an in–depth look at who was selected to occupy elite anti-terrorist positions, what they were trained for, and how they were equipped: when opposing forces are using commercial airliners and chemical weapons, countermeasures are by necessity complicated and varied. CQB takes an intimate look at what it was like to be an officer on alert for chemical attacks in Washington DC, or an army reservist monitoring suspicious activities on the streets of NYC.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E12 - French Foreign Legion
programme.desc: No country other than France operates an elite military force that invites foreign nationals to serve in its ranks. With a reputation for being a safe haven for individuals with questionable pasts, the French Foreign Legion is a true mercenary army that has garnered significant respect within the global special operations community. This episode of CQB examines a raid by the Foreign Legion on a small airport in Iraq during the 1990 Gulf War, exploring the nature of the Legion, how it differs from other special forces, and how it prepares for a wide variety of close quarter battle scenarios in conflict situations around the world.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E05 - Life and Death
programme.desc: Temperate Rain Forest Pt2. Jim comes face to face with a monster black bear in the coastal rain forest of the Pacific Northwest.

programme.desc: Remembering Diana, Princess of Wales includes scenes from her state funeral and heartfelt words from her closest friends. It's a warm and reflective look at Diana both as a person and a public figure: the queen that never was and the princess who'll always be remembered.

programme.title: Harry & Meghan: A Very Modern Romance
programme.desc: Meghan Markle and Prince Harry share similar interests and seem like a perfect match. Both have faced tough times growing up but have come out on top. Now they're winning together. This hour-long special, featuring a chat with author Andrew Morton, explores the social backdrop that makes their bold marriage fit right in with today's British Royal Family.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E09 - Operation Mac Pass
programme.desc: In this episode, the Wardens get a Tip-Mont call about some elk that were taken illegally and go after the suspects.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E10 - Operation Paddlefish
programme.desc: This week, our Wardens are out in Montana keeping an eye on the rivers as folks go paddlefishing, and we're also trying to get rid of a troublesome bear from someone's property.

programme.title: Dropped - S02:E01 - Hell Has A Name
programme.desc: At the start of Season Two of Dropped, we get a closer look at the adventures on the way to Base Camp and sheep camp.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E07 - Living Planet
programme.desc: With continuous observation of arth from orbit scientists have built a data set over time that reveals much about how the Earth breaths and life sustains itself on this living Planet.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E08 - Cosmic Collisions
programme.desc: Cosmic and x rays, these mysterious and highly powerful particles from deep space are being investigated to finally discover where they come from.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E12 - French Foreign Legion
programme.desc: No country other than France operates an elite military force that invites foreign nationals to serve in its ranks. With a reputation for being a safe haven for individuals with questionable pasts, the French Foreign Legion is a true mercenary army that has garnered significant respect within the global special operations community. This episode of CQB examines a raid by the Foreign Legion on a small airport in Iraq during the 1990 Gulf War, exploring the nature of the Legion, how it differs from other special forces, and how it prepares for a wide variety of close quarter battle scenarios in conflict situations around the world.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E17 - Remembering Diana Princess Of Wales
programme.desc: Remembering Diana, Princess of Wales includes scenes from her state funeral and heartfelt words from her closest friends. It's a warm and reflective look at Diana both as a person and a public figure: the queen that never was and the princess who'll always be remembered.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E18 - The Queen Mother An Affectionate Tribute
programme.desc: The Queen Mother, who lived as long as the century itself, was a beloved figure in British life. She was a symbol of bravery during the Second World War and a timeless icon of steadiness, winning a deep affection from people that was only matched by the Queen herself.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E11 - Operation Interstate Game Check
programme.desc: In this episode the Wardens set up a game checkpoint to make sure everyone is following the rules.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E12 - Operation Chuck Coal
programme.desc: Working in remote areas to safeguard our precious natural resources means every day on the job is exciting.

programme.title: Dropped - S02:E02 - Horses Can Think...Rafts Can't
programme.desc: In episode two, Casey continues where they left off. They're faced with a choice. Once they've settled into a risky spot on the mountain, they see that the ram they were after isn't legal to hunt, so they have to retreat.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E09 - Gravity
programme.desc: LISA pathfinder, has led the way for a space based gravity wave detector, what are gravity waves and why are they so hard to detect?

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E10 - Interface
programme.desc: The Ionisphere, where the Earth interfaces with space, is little understood, it effects radio communications, GPS signals and satellites alike, it changes between day and night and is influenced from space and from Earth, The New satellites have been launched to study this zone.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E13 - Hunt and Capture Saddam Hussein
programme.desc: Ten years ago, thousands of US and Coalition forces personnel, ranging from elite soldiers to reservists, found themselves in the middle of two conflicts that required an entirely different approach to warfare than they had previously experienced. From special forces units securing vital points of strategic interest and capturing key individuals in Afghanistan. This episode of CQB takes a close look at how special operations were integrated into regular units and how they fought through many close quarter combat situations with a combination of intelligence, high-tech weaponry and surveillance technologies to find and capture Saddam Hussein.

programme.title: The Luxury Travel Show - S01:E02 - Ice Hotel, Sweden and Bangkok
programme.desc: Ever fancied spending a night in the Ice hotel? We visit the breath-taking man-made winter wonderland and have a look at the arctic activities which guests can enjoy during their stay in Sweden. Then it’s off to warmer climates to Thailand’s capital – Bangkok.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E06 - Heaven's Gate
programme.desc: Kyrgyzstan. Jim and Corey journey to the Tian Shan mountain range in search of high altitude mountain dwelling sheep and ibex.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E22 - Harry The Mysterious Prince
programme.desc: Despite all the media buzz, much of it not exactly flattering, Harry remains a bit of an enigma. This engaging documentary offers fresh insights and footage to shed light on a royal prince who has dealt with both heartache and scandals.

programme.desc: The Queen Mother, who lived as long as the century itself, was a beloved figure in British life. She was a symbol of bravery during the Second World War and a timeless icon of steadiness, winning a deep affection from people that was only matched by the Queen herself.

programme.title: The Flying Deuces
programme.desc: When two bumbling friends join the French Foreign Legion on a whim, they find themselves in a whirlwind of misadventures, love, and laughter as they attempt to navigate the challenges of military life in a foreign land.

programme.title: Perfect Girl
programme.desc: A coming of age romance for anyone who's ever had a crush. Since high school, Stan and Jenny have had crushes on each other. They wrote letters to one another over school holidays but in person they barely spoke; sharing only the occasional lingering glance and smile. Over the years they fantasized about how perfect they would be as lovers. Ten years later they bump into each other and have the chance to make it a reality, but it's not that simple; self doubt, fear of rejection, of losing their fantasies will hold them back from what could be the perfect union.

programme.title: I Would Have Kissed You
programme.desc: Three months after college graduation, best friends Mattie and Olivia are struggling to write a feature and struggling even more with their love lives. Mattie finds herself in a grey area with her college ex-boyfriend while Olivia clings to the hope that her crush will finally want to be with her (despite his hot new girlfriend.) British Web Awards - Awarded "Best Writing in a Dramedy" and "Best Music" Top Indie Awards -Awarded "Best Humor" WRPN Women's International Film Festival - Awarded "Exceptional Merit Award"

programme.title: The General
programme.desc: When Union spies steal Johnnie Gray's (Buster Keaton) beloved locomotive, the General, he pursues them with the aid of his fiance, Annabelle Lee (Marion Mack) straight through enemy lines. One of the most revered comedies of the silent era.

programme.title: Finding Joy
programme.desc: A struggling writer rediscovers himself, his offbeat family, and what it means to be happy when he meets Joy – a spirited, possibly-dying young woman who asks him to write her obituary.

programme.title: Brazzy Jazzy
programme.desc: When a Brazilian Girl takes on the NYC fashion world, her adventures are sometimes sexy, often funny but always Caffeinated! It's Jane the Virgin meets Girls, only an outsider immigrant version - more like Girls of the 3rd World.

programme.title: Growing Op
programme.desc: In an average American neighborhood, a family of four breaks all conformity making it difficult for their 18 year old son to fit in to society.

programme.title: 30 Nights of Sex
programme.desc: In a last ditch effort to save their marriage, Nick and Willa visit a renowned, yet eccentric, couples therapist and embark on a month-long journey of provocative and hilarious sex assignments.

programme.title: 10 Inch Hero
programme.desc: An artist gets a job at a beachside sandwich shop, where she hangs out with a techie, a flirt, a rocker, a hippie, and a Wiccan.

programme.title: Alien Trespass
programme.desc: After crash landing on the outskirts of a desert town, an alien enlists the help of a local waitress to recapture a monster that has escaped the wreckage of his spaceship in this affectionate, knowing, hilarious send-up of a genreís sillier past.

programme.title: Eavesdrop
programme.desc: Ensemble drama about conversations overheard in a bistro: two chess players see unfolding dramas, a couple on an uncomfortable blind date, a crumbling marriage, and film-noir fans that think they're witnessing a real-life murder.

programme.title: Citizen Duane
programme.desc: CITIZEN DUANE is a comedy/drama about Duane Balfour a teen-aged Don Quixote born into a family of spectacular failure. What starts as a simple schoolyard rivalry snowballs out of control when Duane decides to run for mayor of the tiny town of Ridgeway. If Duane is to succeed, he must not only overcome the powerful incumbents, but also his own inadequacies, public perception, and history itself.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - New Zealand
programme.desc: This week we traveled to the beautiful country of New Zealand.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Ding Darling
programme.desc: In this show, we visit the Ding Darling Wildlife Refuge in Florida that serves as home to many exotic birds like the roseate spoonbill, reddish egret and white ibis. Then we travel to Africa where you'll see a cheetah in action and elephants, lions and hippopotamuses in their natural habitat. In Arizona, we'll take you to a special area where thousands of sandhill cranes create a spectacle when they fill the skies every morning. And we'll visit a bayou in Louisiana where alligators, green tree frogs and diamondback water snakes inhabit this unique area.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Wolf Lady
programme.desc: Today’s show on “Wild About Animals” features fascinating stories. First we visit the “Wolf Lady,” a former model who cares for wolves. Next our show features a 3 month-old kangaroo rescued from her dead mother and raised by a caring animal lover. The joey survived for 12 months before breaking her leg. Finally, “Wild About Animals” travels to the Camden Aquarium for a look at sharks, poisonous fish, and beautiful marine life. It is truly an eye opening experience.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Ocean Creatures
programme.desc: Join Emmy Award-winning Actress, Mariette Hartley, as she travels the globe to bring viewers fascinating stories!

programme.title: Whaddyado - BuffaloAttacks
programme.desc: A wild buffalo attacks a spectator at a famous National Park...a tornado hits a busy airport and the passengers need to run for cover...a mother is choking on a piece of steak and her 13 year old daughter must save her...after a high speed chase, a police officer discovers that the reckless driver is only 12 years old...our Moral Dilemma looks at the recent fad of romantic neck biting, an affection that can lead to an infection.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Car Crash
programme.desc: A 13 year old boy is choking on a school bus and thankfully the bus driver knows just what to do. * There’s a bad car crash on multi-lane highway that leads to another crash – what precautions should be taken to protect you and others. * Skateboarding is a popular sport with teenagers but they need to have the correct equipment. * Avalanches are a deadly winter adversary…what do you do if you’re caught up in one…watch.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Hand in Engine
programme.desc: With his hand caught in a boat engine, a man must rely on his teenage passenger for help. * A young man witnesses an accident and must put his newly acquired CPR skills to the test. * Plus, a moral dilemma segment looks at the disturbing subject of dating violence.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Break Up
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: The relationship has run its course – no comes the hard part – breaking up. And we sink our teeth into the growing problem of childhood obesity.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Internet Gambling
programme.desc: This week’s topics include: A nip here and a tuck there, in your teens? And, Internet gambling, are the odds really in your favor? If teens are thinking about it or feeling it, we’re discussing it, in the ChatRoom.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Bad Mother
programme.desc: This week’s topics include: He seems familiar, but will he take them for a ride? And Mom makes an offer that could change the whole party. Is she a cool mom or a poor parent? If teens are thinking about it or feeling it, we’re discussing it, in the ChatRoom.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Bahamas
programme.desc: On this adventure, we’ll soak up some rays in the beautiful Bahamas. First we’ll try some water slides. Then we’ll take a look at the water underneath the surface with personal submarines. We’ll even get an up close look at some sharks beneath the sea. Finally, we’ll end our trip with a great ride on some wave runners.

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Factor Fiction
programme.desc: This episode examines some of the popular notions surrounding the Apollo program and discerns whether they are fact or fiction. These include: were Neil Armstrong’s words when he stepped on the moon scripted by Nasa? Products such as Velcro and Teflon are thought to be invented during the space program: true or false? Did President Kennedy try to work together with the Soviet Union to get a man on the moon? These and more are featured in Fact or Fiction.

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Amiable Strangers
programme.desc: Three very different, uniquely talented men came together to form the crew of Apollo 11. Neil Armstrong, the skilled pilot, Buzz Aldrin, the astronaut with a PhD, and Mike Collins, the well-liked pilot of the command module. This episode looks at all three men, not only in their professional capacities, but their personalities as well. They were, as Mike Collins described them, “amiable strangers.”

programme.title: The Apollo Chronicles - Part 3 - Failure And Fire
programme.desc: In this episode, we take a deep dive into the most harrowing and heartbreaking loss of the program.

programme.title: Tap Out Challenge - Oceanside
programme.desc: On October 15th at the picturesque Oceanside, CA, Charles Rials embarked on an incredible BJJ journey, challenging strangers from all walks of life to tap me out and claim $100. But there was a twist that none of them saw coming! Win or Lose, they got the MONEY!!! What they all shared was the courage to step up, the passion to engage, and the heart of a warrior. This video isn't just about BJJ or the challenge — it's a celebration of the human spirit, perseverance, and the unexpected twists that life (and jiu jitsu) can throw our way. Join Charles in this heartwarming, adrenaline-pumping journey where every challenge was met with respect, and every challenger was met with a surprise. Whether you're a BJJ enthusiast or someone who loves to witness genuine human moments, this video has something special for you.

programme.title: Stuart Cooper Films - The Craig Jones Story
programme.desc:
A short documentary telling the story of Craig Jones' sudden rise to success after his upset victory over Leandro Lo at ADCC 2017. After his breakout performance at ADCC, Craig went on to beat many more big names such as Jake Shields In Polaris, and made it to the finals of EBI, where he had a close finals match against Gordon Ryan. Since then Craig has competed in some of the biggest tournaments in the world and his life has changed dramatically. In this film we see that it wasn't always an easy road for him.
Director Stuart Cooper

programme.title: Tap Out Challenge - Oceanside
programme.desc: On October 15th at the picturesque Oceanside, CA, Charles Rials embarked on an incredible BJJ journey, challenging strangers from all walks of life to tap me out and claim $100. But there was a twist that none of them saw coming! Win or Lose, they got the MONEY!!! What they all shared was the courage to step up, the passion to engage, and the heart of a warrior. This video isn't just about BJJ or the challenge — it's a celebration of the human spirit, perseverance, and the unexpected twists that life (and jiu jitsu) can throw our way. Join Charles in this heartwarming, adrenaline-pumping journey where every challenge was met with respect, and every challenger was met with a surprise. Whether you're a BJJ enthusiast or someone who loves to witness genuine human moments, this video has something special for you.

programme.title: ADCC - Denver Opens
programme.desc: The Opens make their way to the mile high city where the best martial arts from the US look to stake their claim for supremacy as the circuit heats up. In this heart-pounding instalment, we bring you all the action from the epic showdown held in the magnificent city of Denver. Former UFC Strawweight Champion of the World Rose Namajunas known for her exceptional martial arts abilities, Rose is now ready to put her skills to the ultimate test in the realm of grappling. Witness her transition from the cage to the mats, as she grapples her way through some of the most intense matches of her career. ADCC Opens superstar and prodigy 16-year-old phenom, Helena Craver, steps onto the mats to showcase her unparalleled talent. With her sights set on glory, she aims to conquer the teenage, adults, and absolute divisions a feat that has never been done before. In a clash of titans, long time elite grappler Ryan Aitkens, a formidable competitor in his own right, is set to go head-to-head against the multiple-time world champion, Mateus Lutes. Brace yourself for an explosive battle between these two grappling juggernauts, as they leave everything on the mats in pursuit of victory.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: - Cheech & Chong : Puff Puff Laugh
programme.desc: The inventors of stoner comedy, legends Cheech & Chong are still jokin’ (and possibly smokin’). Catch them as they perform some of their funniest bits, recall some hilarious behind-the-scenes stories from their days of filming ‘Up In Smoke’ and host a full bag of the world’s funniest comedians. Included in the special are Last Comic Standing finalist Lavell Crawford, creator and star of the Brit cult comedy The Mighty Boosh Noel Fielding, the ever-opinionated Bill Burr, and Canada’s own rising star Jay Malone.

programme.title: Decline of the American Empire
programme.desc: Hosted by The Daily Show’s favourite Brit correspondent John Oliver, The Decline of the American Empire is the comedy dissection of our neighbours to the South… sort of a hilarious outsider’s State of the Union. It’s the smartest, most opinionated and politically-fuelled show in the lineup show, so get ready to piss your political trousers, speak your mind and have a look at the future, or lack thereof, of the USA.

programme.title: Night of One Million Opinions
programme.desc: Never the introvert, the Angriest Man in America Lewis Black hosts a roster of opinionated comics who just want to be heard, dammit! Along with Lewis spewing his usual bile about the state of everything, Derek Edwards pontificates on his driving frustrations, Dom Irrera thinks alcohol is wonderful, Kathleen Madigan has lost all hope for America, Greg Giraldo rants on about how women have all the power today, and Paul F Tompkins has probably the most incendiary topic of all. You’d be an idiot to miss it… then again, that’s just our opinion.

At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. At Louisville’s Trouble Bar, Kimberly shares her newfound knowledge of Kentucky bourbon production from a tour and tasting at Castle + Key distillery and makes Elsa One Perfect Drink.

programme.desc: In "One Perfect Day in Kentucky," BFF’s Kimberly and Elsa bring their shared competitive streak to the Bluegrass State, facing off to find out who can plan the perfect Kentucky day. Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. Elsa wins the first point, but Kimberly’s ready to up the ante, whisking Elsa away for a thrilling cave kayaking adventure at the Gorge Underground. At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 367 - Up Next Fighting 11 - Middleweight Championship Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 11, the Middleweight Championship, from Southern California. In this episode of UFA, wrestler Armen Piloyan faces striker Diego Perez in a lightweight clash and Steven O'Bryant steps into the cage with Anthony Zaragosa. In the main event challenger Sidiah Parker looks to take the belt from the current champion Curtis Millender. Special guest appearance from the youngest ring annoucer in the world, Cameron Michael "Killer Cam" introduces the main event fighters.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 447 - Up Next Fighting 13 part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 13 part 1 from the Commerce Hotel and Casino in Southern California. First up, striker Bryen Dao takes on brawler Ferrin Marcelin in the featherweight division and Aiden Ingram steps into the cage with Steve Mora in a bantamweight bout. Also on this card Carlos Figueroa looks to break Artem Afanasenko's undefeated streak. In the main event, Christopher "Taco" Padilla puts his lightweight title on the line when he faces his toughest opponent yet with five time UFC veteran Justin Janyes.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 447 - Up Next Fighting 13 part 1

programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 13 part 2 from the Commerce Hotel and Casino in Southern California. Starting off in the bantamweight division, Jonathan Powell steps into the cage with veteran grappler Will Holguin. In a featherweight bout, striker Jonny O'Neill takes on wrestler Eudardo Zarate with the winner moving on to a title opportunity. Also watch as Adam Garcia and Zachary Kraschinsky take to the ring in a lightweight bout. With two titles on the line in the featured bout, the rising star UNF Featherweight title and the California State featherweight title in the rising stars division, Stone Lavelle and his opponient Sean Crenshaw battle it out for the two belts.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 344 - Up Next Fighting (UNF) 8 - Wassmer vs. Lua
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 8 from Southern California. In this episode, Kester Abad faces Dylan Stockard in a flyweight bout and Daniel Labastida and Matheus Santos face off in a bantamweight contest. Also watch as David Babakhanyan takes on Daniel Gualajara and in the main event, Elwig Wassmer, defending title holder and a biochemist looks to take on Israel Lua (Ben Jones camp) with knockout power, in what's expected to be a combustible fight with two titles on the line. The fighters contend for both the UNF flyweight title and the California state championship title.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 347 - Up Next Fighting (UNF) 9 Part 1 - Rivera vs. Wang-Kim
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 9 from Southern California. In a heavyweight bout Sean Sharaf takes on Nathan Mullett and Anthony Romero faces Brandon Aviles. The main event features a title fight between Cisco Rivera with 10 KO's and Contender Series Josh Wang Kim in the bantamweight division.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 359 - Up Next Fighting (UNF) 9 Part 2 - Lilley vs. Strader
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 9 part 2 from Southern California. In this episode after a confrontational weigh in Jesse Strader faces Ryan Lilley in the featured bout. Also watch Jake Babian versus Emanuel Graham, Weston Quiroz looks to take the title from featherweight reigning champion Hamzeh Trad and in a bantamweight contest David Duran fights Narek Avaguan.

In the co-main event, Victor Pisillas is set to meet the challenge with Carlos Jackson in a crossroads fight.

programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 11, the Flyweight Championship, from Southern California. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 356 - CFC Mursa Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Centurion Fighting Championship 16 Mursa part 2 from Malta. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 387 - CFC 18 Praetoris Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Centurion Fighting Championships 18 part 1 from Rio de Janeiro. Karin "Turko" Kanam faces Arnaldo "Black King" Moska in an extreme boxing match. Kellison "Angolano" Souza steps into the cage with Romanti "Joker" Marrota for a welterweight bout and in a female MMA match Yasmin Guimaraes takes on Amanda "Sardinha" Torres.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 388 - CFC 18 Praetoris Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Centurion Fighting Championships 18 part 2 from Rio de Janeiro. Also watch as Luan "Mao De Pedra" Duarte with all eleven wins by KO takes on submission specialist Gabriel "Galindo" Souza.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 389 - CFC 18 Praetoris Part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Centurion Fighting Championships 18 part 3 from Rio de Janeiro.
